Dependencies: Docker Network ai-net is correctly declared as an external prerequisite. Order of operations (Network setup → Ollama → Open WebUI/MCPO → Home Assistant) is structurally sound.

Networking: The architecture correctly routes around the limitations of Docker bridge isolation vs. host-networking. HA targeting Localhost/LAN IP, while Open WebUI uses internal Docker DNS, is logically flawless.

Reproducibility: Once the YAML syntax and directory permission issues are corrected, this setup is entirely deterministic.

